HEADWORD: Catarrhine
<hw>Cat"ar*rhine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>kata`rris</grk> with hanging or curved nose; <grk>kata`</grk> down
+ <grk>"ri`s</grk>, <grk>"rino`s</grk> nose.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of the <xex>Catarrhina</xex>, a division of Quadrumana,
including the Old World monkeys and apes which have the nostrils close
together and turned downward. See <er>Monkey</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catarrhous</ent>⟦br⟧
